    <h2>Marin Certified Organic Agriculture (MOCA)</h2>
    <p>
        <li>MOCA is part of Marin County’s government and was
        developed to provide a professional service to
        local individuals and business operations engaged
        in the production and distribution of organically
        grown products. </li>
        <li>The local agriculture community,
        who promotes sustainable farming practices, is
        served by MOCA. </li>
        <li>MOCA’s main duty is upholding the
        standards of the USDA National Organic Program
        and documenting and verifying operations’ sustainable
        agriculture practices. </li>
        <li>MOCA is a local service that
        promotes production of organic value-added products
        by Marin’s family farms, and this is a benefit to
            Marin’s community of farmers. </li>
    </p>
